{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17636011","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17636011"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T18:22:20+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T18:22:20+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17551"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17551","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17551"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.41,0.45,0.05,0.05,0.05]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10241"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"71407"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10241","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10241"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17551"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56916"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"7"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"34"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"380"},{"type":"tags","id":"2040"},{"type":"tags","id":"2560"},{"type":"tags","id":"3870"},{"type":"tags","id":"4930"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"23948"},{"type":"contributions","id":"23949"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"71407","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/71407"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003ECarpal tunnel syndrome is a common condition caused by compression of the median nerve at the wrist.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following features regarding carpal tunnel syndrome is correct?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Nocturnal symptom exacerbation","High diagnostic accuracy of provocative tests","Preservation of grip strength","Sensory changes affecting all digits","Universal response to splinting"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENocturnal symptom exacerbation\u003C/strong\u003E is typical in carpal tunnel syndrome due to the position of the wrist during sleep, which can increase pressure on the median nerve. Patients frequently report waking up with numbness or tingling in the affected hand.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHigh diagnostic accuracy of provocative tests\u003C/strong\u003E - While Tinel\u0027s and Phalen\u0027s tests are commonly used, they have limited sensitivity and specificity\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPreservation of grip strength\u003C/strong\u003E - Grip strength is often reduced due to median nerve compression affecting thenar muscles\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESensory changes affecting all digits\u003C/strong\u003E - Symptoms typically affect the thumb, index, middle and radial half of ring finger only, sparing the little finger\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EUniversal response to splinting\u003C/strong\u003E - While splinting can be effective, especially at night, response rates vary significantly between patients\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe diagnosis is primarily clinical, based on the characteristic pattern of symptoms including nocturnal paraesthesia in the median nerve distribution.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Carpal tunnel syndrome often presents with symptoms that are worse at night.","Tinel\u0027s and Phalen\u0027s tests have limited sensitivity and specificity for diagnosing carpal tunnel syndrome.","Carpal tunnel syndrome can be associated with a weak grip due to median nerve compression."],"references":["Aroori S, Spence RA. Carpal tunnel syndrome. Ulster Med J. 2008 Jan;77(1):6-17. PMID: 18269111; PMCID: PMC2397020.","Genova A, Dix O, Saefan A, Thakur M, Hassan A. Carpal Tunnel Syndrome: A Review of Literature. Cureus. 2020 Mar 19;12(3):e7333. doi: 10.7759/cureus.7333. PMID: 32313774; PMCID: PMC7164699.","Joshi A, Patel K, Mohamed A, Oak S, Zhang MH, Hsiung H, Zhang A, Patel UK. Carpal Tunnel Syndrome: Pathophysiology and Comprehensive Guidelines for Clinical Evaluation and Treatment. Cureus. 2022 Jul 20;14(7):e27053. doi: 10.7759/cureus.27053. PMID: 36000134; PMCID: PMC9389835.","Singh, V. (2024). Textbook of Clinical Neuroanatomy-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Michael-Titus, A. T., \u0026 Shortland, P. (2022). The Nervous System, E-Book: The Nervous System, E-Book. Elsevier Health Science","Merryman J, Varacallo M. Klumpke Palsy. 2023 Aug 4. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 30285395"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56916"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17551"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56916","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/56916"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-18T15:04:22+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-18T15:05:24+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10241"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"71407"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"7","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/7"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udde0","name":"Neurology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:45+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":